<TITLE> B. league booters to play senior division </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 31 (bdnews24.com) - The Bangladesh Football Federation is planning to allow those footballers who played in fewer than three B. League matches into the senior division football league. "We have a plan to ban the foreign footballers from the senior division league, and to allow those B. league players who played only two or three matches into senior division football," said BFF general secretary Anwarul Haq Helal Tuesday. "The participating 13 clubs have agreed in principle to the proposal and we will take the final decision in our executive meeting on August 4," said Helal. He said the inter-club players' transfer is likely to take place in September and the single-league might begin after the Eid-ul-Fitr. bdn
